sentences: Matthew Barber (born January 10, 1977) is a Canadian singer-songwriter.

Gaining support from the small but committed Hamilton music community, he released his breakthrough album Means and Ends independently in 2002.
The album soon caught the attention of Paper Bag Records, who re-released it to a wider audience in 2003.
After two years in Hamilton, Barber moved to Toronto.
He has toured extensively with artists including Buck 65, BOY, Joel Plaskett, Emm Gryner and Matt Mays and El Torpedo.
Signed to Warner Music Canada, he released the EP title The Story of Your Life in 2004 and the full-length album Sweet Nothing on September 27, 2005.

On March 4, 2008, Barber released his fourth album on Outside Music, Ghost Notes.
His fifth album, True Believer, was released on February 23, 2010.
The self-titled album Matthew Barber was released June 7, 2011, on Outside Music.

In 2014, he released Big Romance.
Barber returned to work in 2018 with Phase of the Moon, his first solo LP in four years.
